Sure, here's a simple example of looping through a list of cars in Java using ArrayList and for-each loop:

```java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Create a list of cars
        List<String> cars = new ArrayList<>();
        cars.add("Toyota");
        cars.add("Honda");
        cars.add("Ford");
        cars.add("BMW");
        cars.add("Tesla");

        // Loop through the list of cars using a for-each loop
        for (String car : cars) {
            System.out.println(car);
        }
    }
}
```

This program creates an ArrayList of car names and then iterates through the list using a for-each loop, printing each car name to the console.

